# My self-hosted stack

This self-hosted stack is generated from the template at: https://github.com/mschoettle/self-hosted

## Getting Started

1. Initialize a Git repository and version changes to your stack.

    ```shell
    git init
    ```

1. Define missing env variables in `.env`
{%- if letsencrypt_challenge == 'dns' %}
1. Add the [environment variables for your DNS provider](https://go-acme.github.io/lego/dns/) to `.envs/letsencrypt.env`.
    - We recommend using [secrets](https://docs.docker.com/reference/compose-file/secrets/) for API keys and passwords
    - We recommend using an [override file](https://docs.docker.com/compose/how-tos/multiple-compose-files/merge/) to merge these settings with the generated compose file and avoid conflicts when updating to a new template version
{%- endif %}

## Updating

To update your stack to a new version, run the following command:

```shell
copier update
```

Or, via the [`uvx command`](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/guides/tools/#running-tools) of [`uv`](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/):

```shell
uvx copier update
```

## Features of this stack

- reverse proxy via [`traefik`](https://doc.traefik.io/traefik/)
    - [Let's Encrypt ACME challenge](https://doc.traefik.io/traefik/reference/install-configuration/tls/certificate-resolvers/acme/#the-different-acme-challenges): {{ letsencrypt_challenge | upper }}
